The portal www.bankovnipoplatky.com, an annual survey of the most absurd bank fees, has now decided to announce a competition for "the most absurd decision or project from the EU workshop".
“We were moved to this latest event, in which the EU plans to adopt a 40 percent quota for women in the administration of large European companies,” said Patrick Nager, the organizer of the survey.
Among the absurdities already put forward for nomination is the recent decision of the European Court of Justice to combine the rates of insurance contributions for men and women.
So far, women have had life insurance benefits because for insurance companies, they are objectively less at risk.
“Further incredible ideas from the EU workshop can be put forward for the competition before the end of this year.
